---+ Install ParacraftSDK
| Author: LiXizhi			   |
| Contact: lixizhi@yeah.net	   |
| Version 1.0  Date: 2015.4.8  |

---++ Install Guide
   * Open ParacraftSDK.sln with visual studio 2013 or above. 

It is recommended to stay up to date with our current source respositories (SourceTree recommended for git):
   * https://github.com/LiXizhi/ParaCraftSDK is the root repository, however it is not complete. 
You need to copy additional files from other repository for any missing files, in order to set up a complete development environment for Paracraft. 

---++ Recommended Tools
Visual studio plugins:
   * NPL Language Service for visual studio: https://visualstudiogallery.msdn.microsoft.com/7782dc20-924a-4726-8656-d876cdbb3417
   * NPL Debugger for visual studio: https://visualstudiogallery.msdn.microsoft.com/7ebe665c-4f1d-41fd-91e1-52176cf2d9db
   * ParaEngine tools for visual studio: https://visualstudiogallery.msdn.microsoft.com/accd022b-ec37-4614-8c08-30e291d28bd5
   * Visual Assist: useful for locating script files.
   * SourceTree (Git client): http://www.sourcetreeapp.com/ 

---++ Third party Tools
If you need to build for android:
   * Install NDK and androidSDK: http://developer.android.com/tools/sdk/ndk/index.html
   * Install cygwin: http://www.cygwin.com/
   * Install python 2.7 or above:  https://www.python.org/downloads/
   * building for iOS is supported on MAC, but not possible for windows at the moment. Please wait for next release of visual studio. 

Setup environment variables:
   * android sdk($ANDROID_SDK_ROOT):		http://developer.android.com/sdk/index.html
   * android ndk($NDK_ROOT):			http://developer.android.com/tools/sdk/ndk/index.html
   * ant($ANT_ROOT):				http://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi
   * java($JAVA_HOME)